                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350406-name-901" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-901" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-901" type="surname" value="CUMMING"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-901" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES CUMMING</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at No. 12, Mapleton-place, St. Pancras. I was in Bedford-square on the 20th of April, and felt a twitching at my coat pocket—I turned and saw the prisoner close to nay back, with my hand<lb></lb>kerchief in his hand—he was endeavouring to conceal it—I seized him, and he threw it down on the pavement to his accomplice, who ran off with it—the prisoner slipt from me—I pursued him, and never lost sight of him till I seized him in Montague-place.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I was going along the square, and a man put the handkerchief into my hand.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183504060126"></xptr>
